name: Queen Latiffa teleports to planet Seikō
description: Queen Latiffa’s ability to teleport to any place in the known multiverse on a whim got the better of her again, while she was talking to the extremely voluptuous ambassador of Fangdor, Samra Gallef, at a private dinner party on Taut VI. The ambassador’s  species is characterized by countless filaments that originate from the back of their head, generating three dimensional symbols and images as a form of speech. Fangorians use this type of visual communication only on two occations: For those who cannot grasp their high pitched sounds, and in their most intimate encounters. This very thought and the ambassador’s tentacle-like filaments  made queen Latiffa teleport straight to Seikō, the home planet of horrific ancient plant-like sentient beings. Most pleasure seekers, who visit Seikō, do so only once and die from sexual asphyxiation. Not queen Latiffa, though. She comes prepared.
